# Python Execution Rule - UV

- Always use the `uv run` command instead of `python` to execute Python scripts
- Correct format: `uv run path/to/script.py [arguments]`
- Never use plain `python script.py` commands

## Examples
- Instead of: `python script.py`
- Use: `uv run script.py`

- Instead of: `python -m module_name`
- Use: `uv run -m module_name`

- Instead of: `python script.py --arg1 value1`
- Use: `uv run script.py --arg1 value1`